Yes, it is. Due to the power of our current computers and our expanded knowledge of computer science, we can make that huge step in a hell of a lot less time than it took us to do the same for classical computers, even with the considerable increase in complexity of quantum-capable wafers. Just consider the amount of money being funnelled into it. For decryption purposes alone the government will spend any amount of money to get it because it gives them a considerable edge.<br />
